-------------
---Shannon---
-------------

Shannon is a pet project to encode plain-text messages into -
 and decode them from - audio files.

--Usage--
Compile shannon.c and link all other c files.
Ensure that executable directory contains directories "noise", "signal", and "inbox".
Place an audio file in "noise" and a plain text file in "signal" to encode.
Place an audio file with an encoded message in "inbox" to decode.
No command line arguments required.

--Error codes--
1: Aborted by user; exited to prevent memory leaks.
2: Failed to read the current working directory.
3: Empty resource directory.
4: Failed to open selected resource file.
5: Noise file too small to contain signal file.
6: Failed to open output file.
